#1601
The Gates of Hell~
@@RMassive gates of scorched iron loom before you, wreathed in crimson flame.
@@RThe iron is etched with the faces of the screaming damned, their mouths agape
@@Rin silent torment. Above the gate, letters of molten fire blaze the words:
@@R'Abandon All Hope, Ye Who Enter Here.' A sulfurous wind howls through the
@@Rgate and the ground beneath your feet radiates an awful warmth. The stench
@@Rof brimstone and charred bone clings to everything. Iron spikes line the
@@Rtop of the gate, each one impaling a wailing shade whose screams blend
@@Rinto the endless chorus of the eternally condemned.
