The Vestibule of Hell~
@@RYou stand in the vestibule between the mortal world and the infernal regions.
@@RGrey shades drift past you, wailing softly -- the souls of those who lived
@@Rwithout praise or blame, condemned to spend eternity here, forgotten by both
@@RHeaven and Hell. The ground is cracked and scorched, wisps of crimson smoke
@@Rcurling upward from fissures in the earth. A yellowed notice board stands
@@Rto one side, its surface covered in proclamations written in hellfire that
@@Rcontinually char the parchment and rewrite themselves. The shades here pay
@@Rit no mind -- they have read it ten thousand times and it has never changed.
