#1630
The Wailing Vaults~
@@RA series of arched vaults extends here, each one sealed with rusted iron
@@Rdoors behind which come sounds of extraordinary specificity -- not general
@@Rscreaming but the articulate cries of those being tormented in ways
@@Rprecisely calibrated to their particular failures. The corridors between
@@Rthe vaults are watched over by daemon archivists who carry ledgers listing
@@Rthe occupant, the nature of their sin, and the torment assigned. They
@@Rexamine these ledgers with the careful satisfaction of those who take
@@Rpride in thorough record-keeping. The vaults themselves are numbered in
@@Ra system that makes no sequential sense, suggesting either an organizational
@@Rphilosophy beyond mortal comprehension or no organizational philosophy at
@@Rall, both of which are equally unsettling in context.
