#1636
The Frozen Wastes of Cocytus~
@@RThe ice of Cocytus extends in all directions, its surface broken by the
@@Rprotruding limbs and faces of the deeply frozen. The wind here is knife-
@@Rsharp and comes from everywhere at once, the beating of Lucifer's wings
@@Rfelt even at this distance as a pressure change that arrives before the
@@Rcold does. The ice itself is of extraordinary clarity, allowing you to
@@Rsee deep into its depths where more frozen figures are visible, stacked
@@Rlike a terrible library of betrayal. The topmost layer is those who
@@Rbetrayed their kin; below them those who betrayed their country; below
@@Rthem those who betrayed their guests; deepest of all those who betrayed
@@Rtheir lords. The categorization is precise and merciless, as all truly
@@Rgood filing systems are. Nothing moves here but the wind. Everything
@@Ris exactly where it deserves to be, which is worse than chaos.
