#1677
The Eye of the Storm~
@@RAt the absolute center of the second circle's tempest, a strange stillness
@@Rreigns -- the eye of the infernal hurricane. The shrieking winds form walls
@@Raround this pocket of terrible calm, close enough to touch and loud enough
@@Rto shake the bones. The ground here is littered with the possessions of the
@@Rlustful, shed as the storm stripped them: rings, locks of hair, pressed
@@Rflowers, love letters charred but still partially legible. A few particularly
@@Rfamed sinners are pinned here in the calm, their torment the knowing that the
@@Rstorm will reclaim them the moment they step beyond this fragile sanctuary.
@@RSome have been in the eye so long they have memorized every letter on the ground.
@@RThey no longer read them. They no longer need to. The words are written in them now.
