The Pit of the Flatterers~
@@RThe second bolgia of Malebolge is crammed with flatterers immersed to their
@@Rcrowns in a river of foul excrement -- the distilled product of all the false
@@Rpraise they dispensed in life. The sinners thrash and wade through the filth,
@@Rtheir voices still shaping compliments even now as they choke and sputter.
@@RThe stench here has a particular quality of embarrassment to it, as if even
@@RHell finds this bolgia somewhat overdone. Demons on the banks toss additional
@@Rflattery back into the trench in the form of physical objects -- wreaths, ribbons,
@@Rphrases of excessive praise made solid -- which sink immediately. The flatterers
@@Rcatch them, delighted, and hold them until they dissolve. Then they reach for
@@Rmore. This is the essence of their punishment and also, if you watch carefully,
@@Rthe essence of why they are here at all. Some things do not change with the venue.
